data.meta_description: Zenaide & Charlotte Bonaparte, daughters of Joseph Bonaparte and Julie Clary, and Napoleon's favorite nieces. Zenaide, front, is 20 and Charlotte 19. Charlotte married the son of her Uncle Louis, Zenaide married the son of her Uncle Lucien. They were raised mostly in Naples and Spain, and after Uncle Napoleon's fall lived 6 years in Frankfurt. In 1821 they moved to Brussels with their mother and married. Both girls eventually lived with their father in America.
